               <p>THOMAS TAGG. I am an <rs id="t18180401-23-viclabel134" type="occupation">undertaker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18180401-23-victim190 t18180401-23-viclabel134"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18180401-23-crimeloc135">Sun-street, Bishopsgate</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18180401-23-crimeloc135" type="placeName" value="Sun-street, Bishopsgate"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18180401-23-crimeloc135" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18180401-23-off132 t18180401-23-crimeloc135"></join>. On the 11th of March, about five o'clock in the afternoon, my great coat hung at the farther end of the shop. I was in the parlour-my wife called out, and I saw the prisoner running out with it - I pursued and took him, and saw him drop it - I never lost sight of him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18180401-23-person191">
                  PETER 
                  BURRELL
               <interp inst="t18180401-23-person191" type="surname" value="BURRELL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18180401-23-person191" type="given" value="PETER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18180401-23-person191" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am officer. I heard the cry, and saw the prisoner drop the coat.</p>
